astooki-lib: astronomical toolkit library
==============================================================================

The astronomical toolkit library is a set of Python libraries which can be
used to process and analyze astronomical data. Currently, the focus is mainly
on wavefront-sensor data, but the aim is to expand this to include other
functionality as well.

This library is distributed in the hope that it will be useful, but WITHOUT
ANY WARRANTY; without even the implied warranty of MERCHANTABILITY or FITNESS
FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE.

Installation
============

This module can be installed using the standard NumPy distutils. Therefore,
simply running

   python setup.py install

will install this module to the default installation location. Running

   python setup.py

will start an interactive installation process.

Version history
===============

20090520, v0.0.1:
   * Initial packaging in distutils.
